    "contentHtml": "<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">💃 Dive into K-pop Dance in Seoul — 2025 Guide</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Want to feel like a K-pop idol for an hour? Seoul offers fantastic K-pop dance class experiences — from beginner-friendly studios to full-fledged academies. Whether you’re a first-timer or looking to improve your moves, here are top spots where you can learn K-pop choreography, meet new friends, and feel the beat of the Hallyu wave.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\" />\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">📍 Top Dance Studios for Tourists</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Here are three standout studios that welcome international visitors and make joining easy:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">🎶 REAL K‑POP DANCE (Hong-dae)</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Located in Hong-dae’s vibrant young-culture district, this studio offers 1.5-hour K-pop dance sessions led by professional back-up dancers. No prior dance experience required and English instructions are available. [oai_citation:0‡REAL K-POP DANCE](https://www.realkpopdance.com/?utm_source=chatgpt.com)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">🎶 1MILLION Dance Studio (Seongdong-gu)</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A globally recognized studio known for its choreographers and viral videos. They offer “Experience K-pop Dance” sessions geared towards foreigners, making it a great choice if you want high-quality instruction. [oai_citation:1‡Etourism Korea DMC](https://www.koreaetour.com/product/seoul-1million-dance-studio/?utm_source=chatgpt.com)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">🎶 YN Company K‑POP Dance Class (Gangnam)</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This studio offers open classes in English and private lessons where you pick the song and choreography. Ideal for groups, friends or solo travellers looking for a more tailored session. [oai_citation:2‡Klook Travel](https://www.klook.com/en-US/activity/76146-kpop-dance-lesson-gangnam/?utm_source=chatgpt.com)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\" />\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">🧭 What to Expect &amp; How to Pick Your Class</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Language &amp; Format:</strong> Many studios offer English-friendly classes. Some like YN Company even list multi-language options for private sessions.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Duration &amp; Cost:</strong> Open classes typically last 90 minutes. Prices start around USD 40-50 for group sessions. [oai_citation:3‡Viator](https://www.viator.com/Seoul-tours/Dance-Lessons/d973-g26051-c32008?utm_source=chatgpt.com)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Level:</strong> These experiences are designed for beginners and fans — you don’t need prior dance training.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Booking:</strong> To secure your spot, book online or via the studio’s platform. Arrive early! [oai_citation:4‡Aclipse](https://aclipse.net/taking-dance-classes-in-korea/?utm_source=chatgpt.com)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\" />\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">🔑 Final Tip</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you’re visiting Seoul in 2025 and want to try something active, fun, and uniquely K-pop: pick one of these classes. Bring comfy shoes, a water bottle, and your favourite idol’s track queue for after class selfie time! You’ll walk out with new moves, maybe new friends, and a memory of being part of the K-pop wave.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->"
